<entry>
<author><name><![CDATA[tepples]]></name></author>
<updated>2013-06-02T12:59:12-07:00</updated>
<published>2013-06-02T12:59:12-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10135&amp;p=112678#p112678</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10135&amp;p=112678#p112678"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Why do DPCM samples have a ROM size limit?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10135&amp;p=112678#p112678"><![CDATA[
NSF itself is theoretically limited to 1 MiB, but the NSF player on the PowerPak can use only 256 KiB. The limit of total sample size in an NES ROM using MMC3, FME-7, etc. is limited by the number of PRG ROM address output pins on the mapper.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sun Jun 02, 2013 12:59 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
