<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Why do DPCM samples have a ROM size limit?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10135&amp;p=112675#p112675"><![CDATA[
If a Famitracker export fails, please report the bug <a href="http://famitracker.com/forum/threads.php?id=2" class="postlink">on its forum</a>.<br /><br />Some games, like Gimmick! use an 8k region at C000-DFFF dedicated to samples. It has two 8k banks, I believe, and whenever  a sample is played the correct bank for that sample gets swapped in.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5165">rainwarrior</a> — Sun Jun 02, 2013 11:49 am</p><hr />
